{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> περκ-άζω</b>, <br /> (πέρκος ={περκνός}) <b>become dark, turn dark</b>, of grapes beginning to ripen, ὀπώρα ἄκραισι περκάζουσα οἰνάνθαις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Chaeremon Tragicus 12.2; ὅταν ἄρτι π. σταφυλή 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 9.11.7, compare “Hymnus ad Isim” 168, LXX.Amos.9.13; ὅταν ἄρχωνται π. οἱ βότρυες 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 3.16.3, etc. \">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]; of olives, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Geoponica” 9.19.2 \">Refs</a>]; of flowers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “Vita Pythagorae - Porphyrii Opuscula” 44. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, of young men, whose beard begins to <b>darken</b> their faces, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Lavacrum Palladis” 76. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>active</i>, <b>make dark-coloured</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 5.2. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8777","accentedUnicode":"περκάζω","shortDef":"to grow dark","mediumDef":"to grow dark","stepGloss":"to grow dark","stepTransliteration":"perkazō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}